-- TAKE A LOOK-Search for lost Malaysian jet shifts after new lead
-- 
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 12:21AM EDT
-- None



March 28 (Reuters) -    Australian authorities are shifting the focus of their Indian Ocean search for the wreckage of the Malaysian jet that went missing with 239 aboard, moving their quest 1,100 km (685 miles) to the northeast after receiving new information from Malaysia.

